FBIS4-3242 "drchi075_v_94002" FBIS-CHI-94-075 Daily Report 29 Mar 1994 TAIWAN Opposition Party To Operate Satellite TV Station Opposition Party To Operate Satellite TV Station OW1904082794 Taipei Voice of Free China in English 0200 GMT 29 Mar 94 OW1904082794 Taipei Voice of Free China English BFN [From the "News" program] [Text] A satellite television station operated by leaders of the opposition Democratic Progressive Party [DPP] will begin broadcasting on 1 July. DPP national assembly member Hsu Pei-lung, general manager of the National Satellite Station, said programs to be broadcast through VHS channels for the fourth TV channel are yet to be released by the government this summer. The station was founded by DPP legislator Chang Chun-hung. Hsu said during the first stage the National Satellite Station will broadcast three to six hours per day. These programs will alternate in one of three languages, Mandarin, the Taiwanese dialect, or English. Hsu said the station will provide a clear alternative to the three other local TV stations with a different variety of programs. He did not elaborate. The news came before the Government Information Office accepted the application for start of the fourth TV station in Taiwan.
